        "## Code: Tensor Transport\n\n### ConditioningZeroOut (`nodes/nodes_z_image_turbo.py`)\n\n```python\nclass ConditioningZeroOut_ZIMG(io.ComfyNode):\n    @classmethod\n    def execute(cls, conditioning):\n        c = []\n        for t in conditioning:\n            d = t[1].copy()\n            pooled = d.get('pooled_output')\n            if pooled is not None:\n                d['pooled_output'] = \\\n                    torch.zeros_like(pooled)\n            n = [torch.zeros_like(t[0]), d]\n            c.append(n)\n        return io.NodeOutput(c)\n```\n\n### Zero-Copy Tensor Transfer\n\nWhen `share_torch=true`, tensors cross the process boundary via PyTorch’s multiprocessing primitives in `pyisolate/_internal/tensor_serializer.py`:\n\n- **CPU tensors** → `/dev/shm` shared memory (`rebuild_storage_filename`)\n- **CUDA tensors** → CUDA IPC handles (`rebuild_cuda_tensor`)\n\nThe host never copies the tensor data. The child writes to shared memory, the host maps the same memory region.\n\n### Isolation Layer\n\nNo custom serializer needed for CONDITIONING or LATENT — `comfy/isolation/adapter.py` handles torch tensors generically via the `SerializerRegistry`.\n"
      ],
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#000"
    },
