      "title": "Incremental changes described here",
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "## Workflow 2: Conditioning + Latent\n\n### What Changed\n\nThree isolated nodes are now connected:\n\n1. **StringConcatenate_ISO** → host CLIPTextEncode (from workflow 1)\n2. **ConditioningZeroOut_ZIMG** → host KSampler negative input\n3. **EmptySD3LatentImage_ZIMG** → host KSampler latent input\n\n### What Crosses the Process Boundary\n\n**CONDITIONING** — a list of `[tensor, dict]` pairs containing the encoded prompt embeddings and pooled outputs.\n\n**LATENT** — a dict with a `samples` key holding a `torch.Tensor` of shape `[batch, channels, H, W]`.\n\nBoth are tensor-bearing types. With `share_torch=true`, these tensors cross via `/dev/shm` shared memory (CPU) or CUDA IPC (GPU) — zero-copy.\n\n### Data Flow\n\n```\nChild Process            Host Process\n─────────────────        ────────────\nCondZeroOut_ZIMG ──────→ KSampler\nEmptyLatent_ZIMG ──────→ KSampler\n         (zero-copy /dev/shm)\n```\n"
      ],
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#000"
    },
